The Logo Agent's job is to generate flashy pentagon and PIA logos in various
sizes, like this:
<p>

<img src="/Logo/?height=24&type=pia">, and this, 
<img src="/Logo/?height=32&type=pia">, and this, 
<img src="/Logo/?height=32&type=dofs">, and this,
<img src="/Logo/?height=32&type=pent">, 
and even these:<br>
<img src="/Logo/foo?height=200&width=210&type=pent"> 
<img src="/Logo/?height=220&scale=2&type=pia"> <br>
; they were generated using:

<listing>
&lt;img src="/Logo/?height=24&amp;type=pia"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/?height=32&amp;type=pia"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/?height=32&amp;type=pent"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/foo?height=200&amp;width=210&amp;type=pent"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/?height=220&amp;scale=2&amp;type=pia"&gt;
</listing>

The only really important parameters are <code>height</code> and
<code>type</code>; everything else is derived automatically, though you might
disagree with the defaults.  You can also use the following, superior format: 

<listing>
&lt;img src="/Logo/pia24"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/pia32"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/pent32"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/pent200"&gt;
&lt;img src="/Logo/pia220"&gt;
</listing>

The <code>height</code> and <code>type</code> in the query string are ignored
in this mode; other attributes are used as usual.  The query string is
optional.<p>

<h3>Limitations:</h3>

Things don't look too good in small sizes; The smallest reliable height seems
to be 20 at the moment, although some smaller sizes can work.  16 is,
fortunately, passable in both <code>pia</code> and <code>pent</code> styles.
Border width is forced to 0 below height=21, which helps.<br>

